\begin{array}{l}\text{What is  reflection, saith my sufferings, then?}\cr \text{If all the pens that ever poets held}\cr \text{Had fed the feeling of their masters' thoughts,}\cr \text{And every sweetness that inspir'd their hearts,}\cr \text{Their minds, and muses on admired themes;}\cr \text{If all the heavenly quintessence they still}\cr \text{From their immortal flowers of poesy,}\cr \text{Wherein, as in a mirror, we perceive}\cr \text{The highest reaches of a human wit;}\cr \text{If these had made one poem's period,}\cr \text{And all combin'd in beauty's worthiness,}\cr \text{Yet should there hover in their restless heads}\cr \text{One thought, one grace, one wonder, at the least,}\cr \text{Which into words no virtue can digest.}\end{array}
